</div>

---

# Johnson et al. ('19),&ensp;.small[*PNAS*]
<p style="text-align: center; color: #A51C30;">"We did not find evidence for anti-Black or<br>anti-Hispanic disparity in police use of force...<br>and, if anything, found anti-White disparities"</p>

<img src="./resources/images/intro_dag_full.png" id="sliddownshrunk" style="position: absolute; left: 2.5%; top: 20%; width: 100%; z-index: ;"/>
???
- first, in terms of fatal shootings, police are "if anything" biased against
  white people
- which may be surprising, if you follow American history
- but for a certain set, this was an extremely popular finding

---

# Johnson et al. ('19),&ensp;.small[*PNAS*]
<p style="text-align: center; color: #A51C30;">"We did not find evidence for anti-Black or<br>anti-Hispanic disparity in police use of force...<br>and, if anything, found anti-White disparities"</p>

<img src="./resources/images/johnsonetal_f1.png" id="sliddownshrunk" style="position: absolute; left: 2.5%; top: 20%; width: 100%; z-index: ;"/>
???
- let's unpack the evidence behind that claim
- actually, the data environment that johnson et al were working with was even more challenging
- they only had data on fatal shootings
---

# Johnson et al. ('19),&ensp;.small[*PNAS*]
<p style="text-align: center; color: #A51C30;">"We did not find evidence for anti-Black or<br>anti-Hispanic disparity in police use of force...<br>and, if anything, found anti-White disparities"</p>

<img src="./resources/images/johnsonetal_f0.png" id="sliddownshrunk" style="position: absolute; left: 2.5%; top: 20%; width: 100%; z-index: ;"/>
???
- if the civilian wasn't shot, or was shot and survived, the encounter wasn't documented

---
# Johnson et al. ('19),&ensp;.small[*PNAS*]
<div class="overlay-container">
  <div class="overlay-text"><h1 class="stroke" style="font-size: 200%">Claim #2</h1></div>
<p style="text-align: center; color: #A51C30;">"White officers are not more likely to shoot minority civilians than non-White officers... increasing diversity... is unlikely to reduce racial disparity in police shootings"</p>
</div>
