<!-- --- -->
<img src="./resources/images/ms_s1.png" style="position: absolute; left: 2.5%; top: 12.5%; width: 100%; z-index: ;"/>
???
- as before, if a stop is made, we get to see the identity of the driver
---
<img src="./resources/images/ms_s0.png" style="position: absolute; left: 2.5%; top: 12.5%; width: 100%; z-index: ;"/>
???
- and if no stop is made, we don't
---
<img src="./resources/images/ms_s.png" style="position: absolute; left: 2.5%; top: 12.5%; width: 100%; z-index: ;"/>
???
- but there's a new twist: the dept of transportation has magnetic sensors
  embedded in the road that tell us how many cars go by
  - so we don't just know that 250 stops were made
  - we also know that there were 1000 vehicles in total, so 25% were stopped
- they record how fast the car is going, too
  - but we'll set that aside for now to keep things simple

