- then we can do the same for the assumption that there are no anti-white stops
- for example, Gelman et al speculated that officers might stop white civilians
  who look out of place in black neighborhoods, on suspicion they were there to
  buy drugs
- it turns out this is quite consequential
- but we don't really believe there is rampant anti-white stopping in New York
