# Automating oversight

- Computational solution to an oversight bottleneck
  - Reduces 10 weeks of derivation to 10 secs. of computation
  - Flexibly adapts to different assumptions, data environments

???
- the real advantage is that this can handle different agencies with completely
  different data environments
- we just got a big grant to take this idea and scale it up into a
  general-purpose diagnostic for traffic discrimination
- that can take in whatever data you have available:
  - shift assignments, traffic sensors, cellphone-tracking data
  - no matter what you have, just throw it in the soup and let the algorithm
    make sense of it
- we've collected a ton of this data for seven of the nation's largest
  agencies and are getting it all ready for analysis
- and the goal is to let us use one unifying method for all of them, rather than
  doing ad-hoc analyses one agency at a time

--
- Ongoing applications to traffic-stop discrimination
