<!-- - here's a problem that's almost isomorphic -->
<!-- - except now the labels are in a survey research context -->
<!-- - say our survey says that 60% of responding democrats support a policy, but -->
<!--   only 40% of responding republicans support it -->
<!-- - but if response rates differ by group: say, you got answers from every -->
<!--   democrat, but NAs for half of republicans -->
<!-- - in a survey setting, we'd be deeply uncomfortable with saying that the groups' -->
<!--   opinions differ -->
<!-- - because for all we know, the missing republicans could be people who like the -->
<!--   policy and are too embarrassed to say it -->

